    "Each group, containing four questions and responses, ensures a thorough evaluation of each model's interpretative capabilities using the uploaded PDF guideline document in the chat tool.",
    "Table 1 illustrates an exemplary question and its corresponding response derived from the clinical questions group.",
    "These questions are accessible from our Github repository.TABLE 1: Example from Clinical Questions Group and Corresponding Response Generated by Pediatric Specialist.Question: What is the proposed cut-point for identifying left ventricular hypertrophy (LVH) by echocardiography in children?",
    "Response:The proposed cut-point for identifying LVH by echocardiography in this age range is ≥45 g/m^2.",
    "Alternatively, LVH may also be defined by the 95th percentile of height normalized for age and sex.The pediatric hypertension guideline [2] contains text, tables, and figures on twelve pages."
